<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="544" pageId="2" pageNumber="543" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1733,1974]" box="[151,751,1733,1758]" pageId="2" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1733,1758]" pageId="2" pageNumber="543">Description.</emphasis>
Length (including wings): male 3.0mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1733,1974]" pageId="2" pageNumber="543">
Crown and lower part of face chocolate brown, face dorsad of antennal bases brownish with dark brown tinge; anteclypeus brownish, apex white; lora and gena brown with white marks. Pronotum brown, with dark brown stripes, apical margin yellowish (
<figureCitation box="[534,600,1841,1866]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[192,1413,436,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,426,1938]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Busonia curvata sp. nov. A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face. Busonia fusca sp. nov. E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and thorax, dorsal view; H, face. Busonia lactata sp. nov. I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241681/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="543">
Fig. 
<number box="[589,600,1842,1866]" pageId="2" pageNumber="543" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Mesoscutum light brown, with basal triangles reddish brown, lateral margin sometimes yellow; scutellum yellowish, white apically (
<figureCitation box="[867,930,1877,1902]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[192,1413,436,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,426,1938]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Busonia curvata sp. nov. A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face. Busonia fusca sp. nov. E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and thorax, dorsal view; H, face. Busonia lactata sp. nov. I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241681/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="543">
Fig. 
<number box="[919,930,1878,1902]" pageId="2" pageNumber="543" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Forewing hyaline with light brown tinge, broad band along costa except a subapical oval, dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[853,928,1913,1938]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[192,1413,436,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,426,1938]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Busonia curvata sp. nov. A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face. Busonia fusca sp. nov. E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and thorax, dorsal view; H, face. Busonia lactata sp. nov. I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241681/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="543">
Figs. 
<number box="[918,928,1914,1938]" pageId="2" pageNumber="543" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B). Mesepimeron brown. Legs brownish, hind leg macrosetae reddish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544">
Male genitalia. Pygofer with height greater than length, dorsal margin with posterior dorsally projected lobe. Appendage of segment X slender, at 
<number box="[583,593,191,215]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[603,619,191,215]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="4.0">4</number>
th curved posteriorly, hook-like, in posterior view not crossing midline. Subgenital plate slender, with several setae apically (
<figureCitation box="[767,836,226,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1673,1695]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,184,1654]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1434,175,1667]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Busonia curvata sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, style, lateral view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view. Busonia fusca sp. nov. F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view; H, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; I, connective, ventral view; J, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241683/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="544">
Fig. 
<number box="[823,836,227,251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Connective with lateral arms short, central lobe rounded. Style tooth on ventral margin nearer basal apex than to distal apex, with several shorter setae. Aedeagus with atrial region as long as shaft, subapical region concave, with a triangle on dorsal margin, several teeth medially in lateral view; aedeagal shaft broad in middle, winglike, square basally, lateral margin of aedeagal shaft curved anteriorly, with a tooth medially in ventral view; gonopore slender (
<figureCitation box="[992,1069,370,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1673,1695]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,184,1654]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1434,175,1667]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Busonia curvata sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, style, lateral view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view. Busonia fusca sp. nov. F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view; H, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; I, connective, ventral view; J, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241683/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="544">
Figs. 
<number box="[1056,1069,371,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
D, E).
</paragraph>
